==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Internment
<hw>In*tern"ment</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F.
<ets>internement</ets>. See <er>Intern</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>Confinement within narrow limits, -- as of foreign troops, to the
interior of a country.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Confining within a country for the duration of a
war; -- usually of citizens of a hostile power.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Internodal</ent>⟦br⟧
